ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: One of the most useful classes. Would definitely recommend it to other students.
A lot of work but worth it. I would recommend this class. I don't think there is any better way to learn the material.

I would absolutely recommend this course to a fellow student, as not only is the material beautiful, but the exercises were often quite fulfilling. Granted, the hints were sometimes excessive, but on the whole I quite enjoyed doing problem sets each week.
This is a very demanding course. If we really want to improve your mathematical skills, then the course is important and recommended. If you are not willing to work hard - forget it.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Extremely important in applied mathematics in general. With a few small exceptions, all of it should be helpful in my research.

This course greatly deepened my knowledge of my discipline. The material in this course comprises roughly 50% of the requisite material for one of our qualifying exams. I'm not yet able to answer how this course will contribute to my research.
I think the course was really important for me and helped me improve my mathematical skills.
